      "message": "wallet: opt out of auto-finalize\n\nPR #28414 added an auto-finalization of PSBTs when callilng\n`walletprocesspsbt` if we think they're complete which is generally\nuseful.\n\nHowever it subverted a check in the case that the `finalize` RPC param\nhad been set to `false`, resulting in a `CHECK_NONFATAL` abort in some\nsituations.\n\nInstead of relying `CHECK_NONFATAL`, decide action based on the result\nof `FinalizeAndExtractPSBT` and return correct \"complete\" status via RPC.\n\nReported in the context of PayJoin transactions in #30077.",
